output.crosstab_text:
For level 8 graduates of Allied health, five years after graduation, the industry with the highest proportion of graduates is the same for both female and male graduates (Education). The median earnings for females in this industry were £38,600 and for males were £43,900.

The biggest difference in proportions is seen in Public administration and defence - compulsory social security where the proportion of male graduates is 4.9 percentage points higher than the proportion of female graduates. The biggest difference in median earnings is seen in Human health and social work activities where the median earnings of male graduates were £25,000 higher than the median earnings of female graduates. The group with the highest earnings was Male graduates who worked in the Human health and social work activities industry (median earnings of £70,000).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Allied health by sex, five years after graduation, male and female level 8 graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2019/20 tax year.
